April 15th is this year's national Day of Silence. More information about this event can be found at http://www.dayofsilence.org/, a site put together by the Gay, Straight, and Lesbian Education Network (GLSEN), or in previous emails from Spectrum. If you are interested in participating, please fill out the following form. There are two options for this year's DoS:
1) Participant: pledges to not speak for the entirety of the day.
2) Support: wears a badge to show their support for the LGBT community.
Form:
https://spreadsheets.google.com/viewform?formkey=dDZGZkluS0tyeC1XNmJmdTl6aGVfTlE6MQ
--Keep in mind that you MUST--absolutely MUST--speak to your teachers BEFORE the Day of Silence.
--Sign-ups are due BY APRIL 12TH. After this date, you can no longer sign up for participating/supporting Day of Silence.

If you have questions, comments, or concerns, please feel free to email any of the board below.

Thanks!
Spectrum Board (Joe Davison, Kelly Wall, and Sarah Weitekamp)
